TY  - JOUR
AB  - In Brock, Lange, and Ozbay (2013), we experimentally investigate social preferences under risk. One of our conclusions is that a social preference model incorporating both ex ante and ex post fairness concerns may best describe behavior. Krawczyk and Le Lee (2016) argue that ex ante comparisons alone may account for our data. We address their points in this reply.
